GOBLIN: Small, cunning survivors of the ruins

Goblins are small, wiry humanoids common throughout the ruins of Rifts
Earth.  Cunning and adaptable, they survive by their wits and their
numbers.  Goblins are found in almost every context: as bandits,
scavengers, merchants, scouts, and occasionally as soldiers or mages.
They have a reputation for deception that is mostly earned.

ATTRIBUTES (APPROXIMATE RANGES)
  IQ: 6-16   ME: 2-12   MA: 3-18   PS: 6-21
  PP: 3-18   PE: 3-18   PB: 3-8    Spd: 7-22

DAMAGE POOL
  SDC: 2d6 x10 (approx 20-120)

SPECIAL ABILITIES
  - Agile and quick; good PP and Spd
  - Adaptable to most environments
  - Above average IQ for their size

PENALTIES
  - Low ME and PB
  - Small stature limits physical presence
  - Distrusted by Coalition and many human settlements

OCC ELIGIBLE: Yes.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

